//@version=6
// ============================================================================
// ORB SYMMETRIC v1 — ungated two-sided opening-range breakout   MNQ / MGC, 15m
// ============================================================================
// WHAT THIS IS — AND WHAT IT DELIBERATELY IS NOT
//   The final product of the 2026-07-05 regime-adaptive research arc. The arc's
//   own permutation tests REFUTED every direction-forecasting layer it tried:
//     - regime-classifier label switching (p=0.79 vs frequency-matched noise)
//     - prior-day SMA50 trend gate       (p=0.15)  } best-in-class but
//     - momentum / gap / confluence votes (p>=0.15) } indistinguishable from
//                                                     the pooled drift
//   What the nulls exposed instead: the SYMMETRIC breakout effect itself —
//   "the first 15m close beyond the 30-minute NY opening range continues,
//   in whichever direction it breaks" — carries the whole edge. This script
//   trades exactly that and nothing else. There is NO trend gate, NO regime
//   detection, NO OR-width filter (tested: wash on MNQ, mildly negative on
//   MGC), and NO warmup requirement. Do not add direction filters without a
//   new permutation-tested validation pass; they are on the refuted list.
//   CONFLUENCES ALSO REFUTED (2026-07-05 pre-registered scan, 20 candidates):
//   ICT (liquidity sweeps, FVGs, killzones, PDH/PDL, midnight/weekly open,
//   NDOG/NWOG) and quant (rel. volume, VWAP, gap size, Monday, NR7, narrow OR,
//   overnight range/inventory, high-vol downsizing) — ZERO survived the
//   permutation + both-symbol + R/yr battery (reports/confluence/04_verdict.md).
//   This script is deliberately filter-free. Take every valid signal.
//
// VALIDATION (reports/sym_validation_note.md + sym_validation.csv; real
// MNQ 2021-2026 / MGC 2019-2026 15m data; commission + slippage included):
//   MNQ NY: avg +0.119R/trade (90% CI [0.089, 0.150]), 57.3% win, n=1245,
//           ~29.5R/yr. Long-days +0.148R / short-days +0.085R, both positive.
//   MGC NY: avg +0.085R/trade (90% CI [0.055, 0.115]), 52.9% win, n=1801,
//           ~20.7R/yr. Long-days +0.074R / short-days +0.098R, both positive.
//   Falsification checks passed on BOTH symbols:
//     fade-null (enter opposite dir, same bar/levels): -0.072R / -0.096R —
//       clearly negative, ruling out a cost/mechanics artifact;
//     entry one bar late: +0.099R / +0.071R — decays, doesn't collapse;
//     5-fold chronological: positive in all 10 folds (worst +0.058R).
//   Funded MC (Tradeify 50k: $2,000 EOD trailing DD, $1,250 DLL, +$3k target,
//   500 block-bootstrap paths of the real daily $ series):
//     MNQ 1 micro: P(target) 85.6% / P(bust) 14.4% / median 80 trading days
//     MGC 1 micro: P(target) 93.8% / P(bust)  6.0% / median 205 days
//     MGC 2 micro: P(target) 74.4% / P(bust) 25.6% / median  98 days
//
// THE TRADE (one decision per day):
//   Chart    : 15-minute, CME_MINI:MNQ1! or COMEX:MGC1! (continuous ticker).
//   OR       : 09:30-10:00 ET (defined as a session WINDOW, not clock math —
//              robust to off-grid opens and partial sessions).
//   Entry    : first 15m bar CLOSE above OR high (long) or below OR low
//              (short), any time 10:00-16:00 ET. First breakout locks the day.
//   Stop     : opposite OR boundary.   Target : 1:1 (= stop distance).
//   Flat     : session end, always. No overnight, ever.
//
// SIZING vs TRADEIFY (reports/01_tradeify_rules_table.md — secondary-source):
//   Default 1 micro. The $1,250 Lightning daily loss limit can only be hit by
//   a single trade's risk (one trade/day), so the maxRiskUSD input is the DLL
//   protection — it skips any day whose OR implies more risk than the cap.
//   MGC at 2 micros roughly halves time-to-target but triples bust risk (74%
//   vs 94% pass) — that trade-off is the user's, not the script's; see tooltip.
//   Session-flat always -> no-overnight rule satisfied. 15m holds -> the >10s
//   scalping rule is irrelevant.
//
// KNOWN OPEN ITEMS:
//   - NOT TV-TESTED. Per the workspace's standing rule after repeated burns:
//     unverified until a live TradingView compile + backtest is reported.
//     Expect roughly one trade every ~1.4 sessions on full loaded history.
//   - B7 half-days: flat-at-session-end is the pre-B7 mechanism. On ~2-3 CME
//     half-days/yr bars stop before 16:00 ET and a position can carry through
//     the 13:00 halt to the reopen. The shelved detectors are NOT here; do not
//     re-add without a live bar-replay test (see Fable Quant/HANDOFF.md).
//   - strategy_v2.pine (MNQ NY, 30m chart) remains the workspace's most-
//     validated strategy (PSR 3.30 sigma, 45/45 CPCV). On MNQ this script is a
//     simpler COUSIN with a different chart/mechanics, not a replacement. On
//     MGC it is the first validated script in the workspace.
//
// ALERTS: one alert, "Any alert() function call". Fires on confirmed bar close.
// Research / advisory only — NOT auto-trading.
//
// CHANGELOG:
//   2026-07-06 f: same SL/TP/entry line-freeze reliability fix as
//     orb_sym_v2's v2b (mirrored here to keep the fixed-mode fallback
//     consistent) — freeze now fires on any flat bar with live handles
//     (self-healing vs a single missed transition bar) and anchors to the
//     trade's actual closedtrades exit bar. DISPLAY ONLY. NOT TV-tested.
//   2026-07-05 e: margin_long/margin_short = 0 in strategy() — disables the
//     broker emulator's margin rejection so every capped signal fills, matching
//     the validated simulator (which sizes by the $575 risk cap, not notional
//     vs equity; 2 micros' notional can exceed the 50k initial capital). Fill
//     behavior can only become MORE permissive; decision logic untouched.
//   2026-07-05 d: header-only update after the confluence scan (20 ICT/quant
//     filters tested, zero survived — script confirmed final as-is). NO code
//     change: decision path, inputs, and visuals byte-identical to build c.
//   2026-07-05 c: visual trade layer — entry labels/arrows, SL/TP lines with
//     shaded risk (red) / reward (green) zones, exit result stamps, risk-skip
//     tags, live OR box. DISPLAY ONLY: the entry/exit/sizing decision path is
//     byte-identical to the validated build (re-audited). Uncapped plot-based
//     SL/TP/entry overlays back up the capped drawing objects in deep history.
//   2026-07-05 b: Lightning-optimized defaults (qty=2, cap=$575) per
//     reports/lightning_playbook.md.
//   2026-07-05 a: initial validated build (see header + HANDOFF.md).
// ============================================================================

strategy("ORB Symmetric v1 (MNQ/MGC 15m NY)",
     shorttitle = "ORB-SYM-v1",
     overlay = true,
     process_orders_on_close = true,
     calc_on_every_tick = false,
     initial_capital = 50000,
     default_qty_type = strategy.fixed,
     default_qty_value = 1,
     commission_type = strategy.commission.cash_per_contract,
     commission_value = 0.62,   // ~$1.24 RT/2 (MNQ); MGC ~$1.20 RT — matches the validated cost model
     slippage = 1,              // 1 tick per fill
     margin_long = 0, margin_short = 0,  // no emulator margin check: every signal under the
                                         // $575 cap must fill, exactly like the validated sim
                                         // (2 micros' notional can exceed 50k equity — TV's
                                         // default margin would silently reject those entries)
     max_lines_count = 500, max_labels_count = 500, max_boxes_count = 500)
// NOTE on drawings: TV keeps only the most recent ~500 line/label/box objects, so
// per-trade markers fade out in deep history. The SL/TP PLOT overlays and the OR
// plot lines have no such cap and follow the chart everywhere you scroll.

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// INPUTS
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
TZ = "America/New_York"

qty = input.int(2, "Contracts (micros)", minval = 1, maxval = 5,
     tooltip = "Lightning-optimized default (reports/lightning_playbook.md): " +
               "BOTH symbols x 2 micros x $575 cap = 85.5% first-payout rate, " +
               "median 51 days, EV +$2,270/attempt. Single-symbol fallback: " +
               "MNQ 2ct (84%/60d). Conservative: 1ct (MNQ 85.6%/80d, MGC " +
               "93.8%/205d). Above 2ct is optimizer-REJECTED (bust rate).")
maxRiskUSD = input.float(575.0, "Max $ risk per trade (skip wider days)", minval = 50,
     tooltip = "Stop distance x point value x contracts, PER CHART. One " +
               "trade/day means this cap is the $1,250 daily-loss-limit " +
               "protection. Running BOTH symbols at the $575 default, the " +
               "worst-case combined day is ~-$1,150 vs the $1,250 DLL — do " +
               "NOT raise this without re-running the Lightning optimizer.")
showPanel = input.bool(true, "Show diagnostic panel")

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// SESSION + OPENING RANGE (window-defined; no clock arithmetic)
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
inSess   = not na(time(timeframe.period, "0930-1600", TZ))
orActive = not na(time(timeframe.period, "0930-1000", TZ))
sessStart = inSess and not inSess[1]
sessEnd   = (not inSess) and inSess[1]

tfOK  = timeframe.isminutes and timeframe.multiplier == 15
isMNQ = str.contains(syminfo.ticker, "MNQ")
isMGC = not isMNQ and str.contains(syminfo.ticker, "MGC")
symOK = isMNQ or isMGC
cfgOK = tfOK and symOK

var float orHi = na
var float orLo = na
var bool  orSeen = false
var bool  locked = false
var int nSessions = 0
var int nEntries = 0
var int nRiskSkips = 0

// live-position state (display only — order levels are set at entry via strategy.exit)
var float posEntry = na
var float posStop  = na
var float posTgt   = na
var int   posSide  = 0
// per-trade drawing handles
var line  lnEntry = na
var line  lnStop  = na
var line  lnTgt   = na
var box   orBox   = na

if sessStart
    orHi := na
    orLo := na
    orSeen := false
    locked := false
    nSessions += 1
if orActive
    orHi := na(orHi) ? high : math.max(orHi, high)
    orLo := na(orLo) ? low : math.min(orLo, low)
    orSeen := true

// OR is tradeable once the window has passed, this bar is still in-session,
// and the range is sane. No other conditions exist — by design.
orDone = inSess and not orActive and orSeen and not na(orHi) and orHi > orLo

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// ONE-SHOT SYMMETRIC BREAKOUT
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
canTrade  = orDone and not locked and cfgOK and strategy.position_size == 0
longBrk   = canTrade and close > orHi
shortBrk  = canTrade and close < orLo

if longBrk or shortBrk
    side    = longBrk ? 1 : -1
    entryPx = close
    riskPts = longBrk ? entryPx - orLo : orHi - entryPx
    riskUSD = riskPts * syminfo.pointvalue * qty
    if riskPts > 0 and riskUSD <= maxRiskUSD
        stopPx = entryPx - side * riskPts
        tgtPx  = entryPx + side * riskPts
        if longBrk
            strategy.entry("L", strategy.long, qty = qty, comment = "OR-break long")
            strategy.exit("Lx", "L", stop = stopPx, limit = tgtPx)
        else
            strategy.entry("S", strategy.short, qty = qty, comment = "OR-break short")
            strategy.exit("Sx", "S", stop = stopPx, limit = tgtPx)
        // ---- visual layer (display only, no order logic) ----
        posEntry := entryPx
        posStop  := stopPx
        posTgt   := tgtPx
        posSide  := side
        // clean lines only — no price labels; extend right so the levels are
        // unmissable ahead of price while the trade is live
        lnEntry := line.new(bar_index, entryPx, bar_index + 1, entryPx,
             color = color.new(color.gray, 20), style = line.style_dotted, width = 1,
             extend = extend.right)
        lnStop := line.new(bar_index, stopPx, bar_index + 1, stopPx,
             color = color.new(color.red, 0), style = line.style_solid, width = 3,
             extend = extend.right)
        lnTgt := line.new(bar_index, tgtPx, bar_index + 1, tgtPx,
             color = color.new(color.green, 0), style = line.style_solid, width = 3,
             extend = extend.right)
        linefill.new(lnEntry, lnTgt,  color.new(color.green, 88))   // reward zone
        linefill.new(lnEntry, lnStop, color.new(color.red, 90))     // risk zone
        nEntries += 1
        alert("ORB-SYM " + (longBrk ? "LONG " : "SHORT ") + syminfo.ticker +
              " qty=" + str.tostring(qty) +
              " entry~" + str.tostring(entryPx, format.mintick) +
              " SL=" + str.tostring(stopPx, format.mintick) +
              " TP=" + str.tostring(tgtPx, format.mintick) +
              " risk$~" + str.tostring(riskUSD, "#") +
              " (signal = confirmed 15m close; fills lag)",
              alert.freq_once_per_bar_close)
    else
        nRiskSkips += 1
        // skipped entry: the whole opening-range zone turns red for the day
        if not na(orBox)
            box.set_bgcolor(orBox, color.new(color.red, 82))
            box.set_border_color(orBox, color.new(color.red, 30))
    // ANY first breakout locks the day — including risk-skipped ones —
    // matching the validated one-decision-per-day simulation exactly.
    locked := true

// extend the live trade's lines while the position is open; stamp the result on exit.
// Freeze fires on ANY flat bar where the handles are still live (not only the single
// bar where position_size is first observed to transition to 0) -- self-healing against
// a missed transition bar (e.g. a data gap around a session boundary), which previously
// could leave a line's extend=right set forever with nothing left to clear it. Anchored
// to the trade's actual recorded exit bar via strategy.closedtrades, not "this bar", so
// the line stops exactly at the exit rather than wherever the flat check happened to fire.
if strategy.position_size != 0 and not na(lnStop)
    line.set_x2(lnEntry, bar_index)
    line.set_x2(lnStop, bar_index)
    line.set_x2(lnTgt, bar_index)
if strategy.position_size == 0 and not na(lnStop)
    exitBarIdx = strategy.closedtrades > 0 ?
         strategy.closedtrades.exit_bar_index(strategy.closedtrades - 1) : bar_index
    line.set_extend(lnEntry, extend.none), line.set_x2(lnEntry, exitBarIdx)
    line.set_extend(lnStop, extend.none),  line.set_x2(lnStop, exitBarIdx)
    line.set_extend(lnTgt, extend.none),   line.set_x2(lnTgt, exitBarIdx)
    lastPnl = strategy.closedtrades > 0 ?
         strategy.closedtrades.profit(strategy.closedtrades - 1) : 0.0
    label.new(bar_index, close,
         (lastPnl >= 0 ? "✔ +$" : "✘ −$") + str.tostring(math.abs(lastPnl), "#"),
         style = posSide == 1 ? label.style_label_down : label.style_label_up,
         color = lastPnl >= 0 ? color.new(color.green, 25) : color.new(color.red, 25),
         textcolor = color.white, size = size.small)
    posEntry := na
    posStop := na
    posTgt := na
    posSide := 0
    lnEntry := na
    lnStop := na
    lnTgt := na

// Force-flat at session end: pre-B7 mechanism only (see header KNOWN OPEN
// ITEMS before touching this line).
if sessEnd and strategy.position_size != 0
    strategy.close_all(comment = "session flat")

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// VISUALS + PANEL
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// OR box: shaded while forming, frozen once complete (drawing — fades in deep history)
if orActive and na(orBox)
    orBox := box.new(bar_index, high, bar_index, low,
         bgcolor = color.new(color.blue, 88), border_color = color.new(color.blue, 40))
if orActive and not na(orBox)
    box.set_rightbottom(orBox, bar_index, orLo)
    box.set_top(orBox, orHi)
if sessStart
    orBox := na

// OR levels as PLOTS — uncapped, follow the chart into deep history
plot(orDone ? orHi : na, "OR high", color = color.new(color.teal, 0),  style = plot.style_linebr)
plot(orDone ? orLo : na, "OR low",  color = color.new(color.maroon, 0), style = plot.style_linebr)

// live SL/TP as PLOTS while a position is open (uncapped backup to the lines)
inPos = strategy.position_size != 0
plot(inPos ? posStop : na, "Stop (live)",   color = color.new(color.red, 30),
     style = plot.style_linebr, linewidth = 2)
plot(inPos ? posTgt : na,  "Target (live)", color = color.new(color.green, 30),
     style = plot.style_linebr, linewidth = 2)
plot(inPos ? posEntry : na, "Entry (live)", color = color.new(color.gray, 40),
     style = plot.style_linebr)

// entry arrows — plotshapes are uncapped and survive full history
plotshape(nEntries > nEntries[1] and posSide == 1,  "Long entry",  style = shape.triangleup,
     location = location.belowbar, color = color.new(color.green, 0), size = size.normal,
     text = "LONG", textcolor = color.new(color.green, 0))
plotshape(nEntries > nEntries[1] and posSide == -1, "Short entry", style = shape.triangledown,
     location = location.abovebar, color = color.new(color.red, 0), size = size.normal,
     text = "SHORT", textcolor = color.new(color.red, 0))

bgcolor(orActive ? color.new(color.blue, 92) : na)

var table pnl = table.new(position.top_right, 2, 5, border_width = 1)
if showPanel and barstate.islast
    table.cell(pnl, 0, 0, "Config"), table.cell(pnl, 1, 0,
         (tfOK ? "15m OK" : "WRONG TF — NEED 15m") + " / " +
         (isMNQ ? "MNQ" : isMGC ? "MGC" : "UNSUPPORTED SYMBOL"),
         text_color = cfgOK ? color.gray : color.red,
         bgcolor = cfgOK ? na : color.new(color.red, 80))
    table.cell(pnl, 0, 1, "Status"), table.cell(pnl, 1, 1,
         not cfgOK ? "CONFIG ERROR — NO TRADES WILL FIRE" :
         locked ? "LOCKED (day done)" : orDone ? "ARMED" : orActive ? "OR FORMING" : "OFF-SESSION",
         text_color = cfgOK ? color.gray : color.red)
    table.cell(pnl, 0, 2, "Sessions / entries / risk-skips"),
         table.cell(pnl, 1, 2, str.tostring(nSessions) + " / " + str.tostring(nEntries) + " / " + str.tostring(nRiskSkips))
    table.cell(pnl, 0, 3, "Entry rate (expect ~0.7/session)"),
         table.cell(pnl, 1, 3, nSessions > 0 ? str.tostring(nEntries / float(nSessions), "#.##") : "-")
    table.cell(pnl, 0, 4, "Net profit"),
         table.cell(pnl, 1, 4, str.tostring(strategy.netprofit, "#.##"),
         text_color = strategy.netprofit >= 0 ? color.green : color.red)
